I’ll now return you all to the regular schedule of retweets of amazing and inspiring works of art interspersed with my own splashing of paint upon plastic 😂

Just got out of weird slump that was mix of just a lot of bad brain days and stressful work bs. But it did at least give me time to help sort some of my thoughts out stuff like this, so I’ll take that as a win.

So far it seems just sticking with a low pressure but defined goal of “let’s aim for x amount of hobby time today” works the best. Also gonna start to work on adding in some WIP pic goals too, hoping it helps to keep me going if I hit a slump.

But on the flip side, I love keeping track of models that I’ve done. But even then it’s a weird fine line between fun numbers and “why’ll aren’t I doing more?”Which cab make me drop a hobby faster than I can blink.

So, I have started a hobby streak about three times now an I think I’m gonna stop trying them. The pressure that goes along with them just pings my ADHD something fierce. Forgetting to post a photo or missing a day makes me feel like garbage even when I get a ton done that day.
